Thoughtcast is a personal notetaking utility written as a major mode into emacs.


To Use:

load thoughtcast.el into emacs. The main function is interactive so you can call it with M-x thought.

You will be prompted for a course of action, select 1 and follow the prompts. If you do not have a directory structures set up to hold files thoughtcast will create one in ~/thoughtcast/

within this directory there are some sub directories

/meals/
/thoughts/
/sleep/

each contains data that you have recorded. 


